  "agent_output": "The ADR already exists and is well-structured. It covers all the key points from MJ's decision note. Here's what's already captured:\n\n- **Context**: Single-node to multi-node expansion, need for batch coordination\n- **Decision**: PostgreSQL advisory locks (`pg_try_advisory_lock`)\n- **Rationale**: No new infrastructure, sufficient for workload, simple failure semantics\n- **Alternatives**: Redis SETNX, ZooKeeper, custom heartbeat table -- all with clear rejection reasons\n- **Trade-offs**: Lock visibility, no TTL, session scope risks\n- **Consequences**: Implementation pattern, monitoring guidance, future revisit trigger\n\nThis ADR is already complete and faithfully captures MJ's architecture decision. No changes needed -- it translates MJ's note into a clean, standard ADR format with the right level of detail. The only thing I'd flag is that the date says `2026-03-19`, which is accurate if that's when MJ made the decision.\n\nWant me to adjust anything -- date, status, add more detail to any section, or add additional consequences?",
